RULES
════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. .hero-section { overflow: hidden } clips hero
   content to its own boundary — this is what
   prevents text bleeding into the next section
   during scroll. Do NOT remove this.

2. The ::before fade on .cards-section uses 
   position: absolute with top: -80px — this
   creates the smooth gradient transition between
   hero and cards without a hard visual cut.
   The -80px pulls it above the section boundary.

3. background: transparent on persona :host is
   mandatory. The semi-transparent overlay goes
   on .persona-content::before with position: fixed
   NOT on :host — fixed positioning means it covers
   the full viewport regardless of scroll position.

4. white-space: nowrap on .persona-label-role is
   the correct fix for "Associat / e" breaking.
   Do NOT use max-width to constrain it — that
   caused the break. Remove max-width entirely.

5. transform-origin on SVG rings stays at 60px 60px
   (center of the 120x120 viewBox) regardless of
   the CSS element size. SVG transforms are in
   viewBox coordinate space, not element space.

